{{en-verb|to mouse|mouses|moused|mousing}}

# (''intransitive'') To move cautiously or furtively, in the manner of a mouse (the rodent); frequently used in the phrasal verb '''to [[mouse around]]'''.
# (''intransitive'') To hunt or catch mice (the rodents).
<!--Disputed:
# (''intransitive'') {{computing}} To operate a [[computer]] using a mouse (the input device).
-->
# (''transitive'', ''nautical'') To close the mouth of a [[hook]] by a careful binding of [[marline]] or wire.
#:''Captain Higgins '''moused''' the hook with a bit of [[marline]] to prevent the [[block]] [[becket]]s from falling out under slack.''

